thread.title: Iowa Presses States’ Ability to Skirt the Health Law

author: Anna Wilde Mathews
title: Iowa Presses States’ Ability to Skirt the Health Law

organizations.name: iowa presses states’ ability to skirt the health law new

text:
New health-insurance legislation in Iowa will become the latest test of the ability of states to allow coverage that doesn’t comply with the federal Affordable Care Act.
Iowa Gov. Kim Reynolds is expected to soon sign into law a bill that would allow the Iowa Farm Bureau, a nonprofit, to offer health coverage that would fall outside the ACA’s rules.
